segment.source: To effectively manage the Application Virtualization System, you can use the Application Virtualization Server Management Console to generate a variety of reports that provide information about the system.
segment.target: To effectively manage the Application Virtualization System, you can use the Application Virtualization Server Management Console to generate a variety of reports that provide information about the system.

segment.source: This information includes daily usage information for a specific application or all applications, and system error tracking.
segment.target: This information includes daily usage information for a specific application or all applications, and system error tracking.

segment.source: Note
segment.target: Note

segment.source: During installation, the installation script installs only the English language version of report viewer.
segment.target: During installation, the installation script installs only the English language version of report viewer.

segment.source: For the report viewer to display the correct information in other languages, it is necessary to install a language pack from the following location: http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=131645.
segment.target: For the report viewer to display the correct information in other languages, it is necessary to install a language pack from the following location: http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=131645.

segment.source: When you add or edit an application in the Server Management Console, you must make sure that the application names and versions exactly match those in the OSD files.
segment.target: When you add or edit an application in the Server Management Console, you must make sure that the application names and versions exactly match those in the OSD files.

segment.source: The reporting feature uses the application names and versions data fields when it identifies application usage data on which to report.
segment.target: The reporting feature uses the application names and versions data fields when it identifies application usage data on which to report.

segment.source: If the data fields do not match, the usage records will be skipped.
segment.target: If the data fields do not match, the usage records will be skipped.
